---
import Layout from '@/components/astro/Layout.astro';
import { supabase } from '@/lib/supabase';
import { DollarSign, TrendingUp, AlertCircle, CheckCircle, XCircle, Calculator } from 'lucide-react';

// Fetch some real data to ground our guide
const { data: lobbyists, error } = await supabase
  .from('lobbyists')
  .select('subscription_tier, is_claimed')
  .eq('is_active', true);

const totalLobbyists = lobbyists?.length || 0;
const claimedLobbyists = lobbyists?.filter(l => l.is_claimed).length || 0;

const pageTitle = 'How Much Does a Lobbyist Cost in Texas? 2025 Pricing Guide';
const pageDescription = 'Complete breakdown of Texas lobbyist costs: monthly retainers from $5K-$50K, what drives prices higher, hidden expenses, and how to calculate ROI on your lobbying investment.';

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: pageTitle,
  description: pageDescription,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'TexasLobby.org',
  },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'TexasLobby.org',
    logo: {
      '@type': 'ImageObject',
      url: 'https://texaslobby.org/logo.png',
    },
  },
  datePublished: '2025-01-06',
  dateModified: '2025-01-06',
};
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} schema={schema}>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-texas-blue-500/5 to-background py-16 border-b border-border">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl">
      <div class="mb-6">
        <a
          href="/guides"
          class="inline-flex items-center text-sm text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline mb-4"
        >
          ‚Üê Back to all guides
        </a>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
        How Much Does a Lobbyist Cost in Texas?
      </h1>

      <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground mb-8">
        The complete 2025 pricing guide: what you'll really pay, what drives costs up (or down),
        and how to know if you're getting a fair deal.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <DollarSign className="h-4 w-4" />
          <span>Updated January 2025</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <TrendingUp className="h-4 w-4" />
          <span>15 min read</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

        <!-- Table of Contents -->
        <div class="not-prose bg-muted/50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">What You'll Learn</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><a href="#quick-answer" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">The Quick Answer (TL;DR)</a></li>
            <li><a href="#pricing-models" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">Four Pricing Models Explained</a></li>
            <li><a href="#real-costs" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">What You'll Actually Pay (The Real Numbers)</a></li>
            <li><a href="#cost-drivers" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">What Makes Lobbying More Expensive</a></li>
            <li><a href="#hidden-costs" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">Hidden Costs Nobody Tells You About</a></li>
            <li><a href="#by-experience" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">Pricing by Lobbyist Experience Level</a></li>
            <li><a href="#red-flags" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">Pricing Red Flags to Watch For</a></li>
            <li><a href="#roi" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">How to Calculate Your ROI</a></li>
            <li><a href="#negotiating" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">Can You Negotiate? (Yes, Here's How)</a></li>
            <li><a href="#budget-alternatives" class="text-texas-blue-500 hover:underline">What If You Can't Afford a Lobbyist?</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Quick Answer -->
        <div id="quick-answer" class="not-prose scroll-mt-24">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">The Quick Answer</h2>
        </div>

        <p class="lead">
          <strong>Most Texas lobbyists charge between $5,000 and $25,000 per month on a retainer basis.</strong>
          You'll typically commit to at least one legislative session (5 months), though many contracts run for a full year
          or even the entire 2-year biennium.
        </p>

        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-border overflow-hidden">
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 divide-x divide-border">
              <div class="p-6">
                <div class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground mb-2">Budget Range</div>
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-1">$5K‚Äì$10K/mo</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Solo practitioners, newer lobbyists, or simple monitoring</div>
              </div>
              <div class="p-6 bg-texas-blue-500/5">
                <div class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground mb-2">Mid-Range (Most Common)</div>
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-1">$10K‚Äì$25K/mo</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Experienced lobbyists, active advocacy on multiple bills</div>
              </div>
              <div class="p-6">
                <div class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground mb-2">Premium</div>
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-1">$25K‚Äì$50K+/mo</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Large firms, former legislators, high-stakes issues</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          <strong>For a typical legislative session engagement</strong> (January through May), expect to invest anywhere
          from <strong>$25,000 to $125,000+</strong>, depending on the complexity of your issue and the experience level
          of your lobbyist.
        </p>

        <!-- Pricing Models -->
        <div id="pricing-models" class="not-prose scroll-mt-24">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">Four Pricing Models Explained</h2>
        </div>

        <p>
          Texas lobbyists typically work under one of four pricing structures. Understanding these will help you
          evaluate proposals and compare apples to apples.
        </p>

        <!-- Model 1: Monthly Retainer -->
        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border-2 border-texas-blue-500 p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-texas-blue-500 text-white rounded-full p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-lg font-bold">1</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Monthly Retainer (Most Common)</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
                  You pay a fixed monthly fee for ongoing representation and advocacy.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                      <CheckCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
                      Advantages
                    </div>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Predictable budgeting</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Lobbyist always available</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ No surprise bills</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Relationship building over time</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                      <XCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
                      Disadvantages
                    </div>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Pay even during slow periods</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Usually requires 3-12 month minimum</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Can be expensive if issue is simple</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm">
                    <strong>Typical contract:</strong> $12,000/month for the 5-month session (January‚ÄìMay) = $60,000 total
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Model 2: Hourly Rate -->
        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-border p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-muted text-foreground rounded-full p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-lg font-bold">2</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Hourly Rate (Less Common)</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
                  You pay for actual time spent, similar to hiring an attorney.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                      <CheckCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
                      Advantages
                    </div>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Pay only for work done</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Good for one-time issues</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Flexibility to increase/decrease</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                      <XCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
                      Disadvantages
                    </div>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Unpredictable costs</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Lobbyist may prioritize retainer clients</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Tracking hours can be tedious</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Hard to build relationships</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm">
                    <strong>Typical rates:</strong> $150‚Äì$500/hour depending on experience. Expect 10-40 hours per month during session.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Model 3: Project-Based Fee -->
        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-border p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-muted text-foreground rounded-full p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-lg font-bold">3</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Project-Based Fee</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
                  A flat fee for a specific, defined objective (e.g., "Get HB 1234 passed").
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                      <CheckCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
                      Advantages
                    </div>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Clear scope and price</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Good for well-defined goals</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Shared risk with lobbyist</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                      <XCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
                      Disadvantages
                    </div>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Scope creep can cause disputes</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Hard to price accurately</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Few lobbyists offer this</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm">
                    <strong>Typical project:</strong> $30,000‚Äì$75,000 for a session-long effort on a specific bill
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Model 4: Success Fee / Contingency -->
        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-red-200 p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded-full p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-lg font-bold">4</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Success Fee / Contingency (Controversial)</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
                  Payment only if specific outcome is achieved (e.g., bill passes or fails).
                </p>

                <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
                  <div class="flex gap-2">
                    <AlertCircle className="h-5 w-5 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" />
                    <div>
                      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-900 mb-1">‚ö†Ô∏è Ethical Concerns</p>
                      <p class="text-sm text-red-800">
                        Many experienced lobbyists won't work on contingency because legislative outcomes depend
                        on many factors beyond their control. <strong>Be very wary of anyone who guarantees results.</strong>
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                      <CheckCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
                      Advantages
                    </div>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ No payment if unsuccessful</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Aligns incentives</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Lower upfront risk</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                      <XCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
                      Disadvantages
                    </div>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Very expensive if successful</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Lobbyist may take shortcuts</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ Most reputable lobbyists refuse this</li>
                      <li>‚Ä¢ "Success" can be subjectively defined</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm">
                    <strong>Typical structure:</strong> 20-50% of the economic value of success (e.g., $100K if your bill would save you $500K)
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- What You'll Actually Pay -->
        <div id="real-costs" class="not-prose scroll-mt-24">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">What You'll Actually Pay: Real-World Scenarios</h2>
        </div>

        <p>
          Let's get specific. Here's what different types of clients typically spend, based on their needs
          and the lobbyist's experience level.
        </p>

        <!-- Scenario 1 -->
        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Small Business, Bill Monitoring Only</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 mb-3">
                  <strong>Client:</strong> 50-person manufacturing company<br />
                  <strong>Need:</strong> Track legislation that might affect them, no active advocacy<br />
                  <strong>Lobbyist:</strong> Solo practitioner with 5-10 years experience
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-1">$5,000‚Äì$7,500/month</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-blue-700">$25,000‚Äì$37,500 for 5-month session</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Scenario 2 -->
        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-purple-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Trade Association, Active Advocacy</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm text-purple-800 mb-3">
                  <strong>Client:</strong> State trade association with 200 members<br />
                  <strong>Need:</strong> Support 3 bills, oppose 2 bills, monitor 20+ more<br />
                  <strong>Lobbyist:</strong> Experienced firm with 3-5 lobbyists on team
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-900 mb-1">$15,000‚Äì$25,000/month</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-purple-700">$75,000‚Äì$125,000 for 5-month session</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-purple-600 mt-2">Often extends to full-year contract: $180K‚Äì$300K</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Scenario 3 -->
        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-green-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Major Corporation, Multiple Issues</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm text-green-800 mb-3">
                  <strong>Client:</strong> Fortune 500 company with Texas operations<br />
                  <strong>Need:</strong> Protect interests across tax, healthcare, employment, environmental issues<br />
                  <strong>Lobbyist:</strong> Top-tier firm with former legislators, year-round engagement
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-900 mb-1">$30,000‚Äì$50,000+/month</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-green-700">$360,000‚Äì$600,000+ per year</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-green-600 mt-2">Plus: Political contributions, coalition memberships</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Scenario 4 -->
        <div class="not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-orange-900 mb-3">Scenario 4: Nonprofit, Single High-Stakes Bill</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm text-orange-800 mb-3">
                  <strong>Client:</strong> Statewide advocacy nonprofit<br />
                  <strong>Need:</strong> Pass one priority bill, lots of coalition coordination<br />
                  <strong>Lobbyist:</strong> Mid-level firm with subject matter expertise
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-orange-900 mb-1">$8,000‚Äì$15,000/month</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-orange-700">$40,000‚Äì$75,000 for 5-month session</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-orange-600 mt-2">May get discounted "mission-driven" rate</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Cost Drivers -->
        <div id="cost-drivers" class="not-prose scroll-mt-24">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">What Makes Lobbying More Expensive?</h2>
        </div>

        <p>
          Understanding what drives costs up (or down) helps you evaluate whether a quote is fair‚Äîand
          where you might be able to save money.
        </p>

        <div class="not-prose my-8 space-y-4">
          <!-- Driver 1 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-texas-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <TrendingUp className="h-6 w-6" />
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">1. The Lobbyist's Network ("Rolodex Value")</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
                  The famous "revolving door" is real. Former legislators, legislative staff, and agency officials
                  command premium rates because they have direct personal relationships with decision-makers.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm"><strong>Price impact:</strong> A former state representative might charge 2-3x what a equally talented "outsider" lobbyist charges‚Äîand they're often worth it.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Driver 2 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-texas-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <TrendingUp className="h-6 w-6" />
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">2. Issue Complexity and Controversy</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
                  A technical tweak to an obscure statute? Relatively cheap. Trying to legalize something currently
                  banned or substantially change tax policy? Buckle up.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm"><strong>Price impact:</strong> Controversial issues can cost 50-100% more because they require more coalition-building, more meetings, more opposition research, and more time testifying.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Driver 3 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-texas-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <TrendingUp className="h-6 w-6" />
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">3. Number of Bills to Track</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
                  During a typical legislative session, 6,000-7,000 bills get filed. If your interests are broad
                  (e.g., you're a large trade association), your lobbyist needs to monitor hundreds of bills.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm"><strong>Price impact:</strong> Monitoring alone: +$2K-$5K/month. Active work on 5+ bills: +$5K-$15K/month.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Driver 4 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-texas-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <TrendingUp className="h-6 w-6" />
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">4. Timing and Urgency</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
                  Hiring a lobbyist in November before session starts in January? Normal pricing. Calling one
                  in March when your bill is about to get a committee hearing? Expect to pay a premium.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm"><strong>Price impact:</strong> Last-minute engagements can cost 25-50% more, if the lobbyist even has capacity to take you on.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Driver 5 -->
          <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="bg-texas-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                <TrendingUp className="h-6 w-6" />
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">5. Firm Size and Overhead</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
                  Large firms with 20+ lobbyists, downtown Austin offices, and lots of support staff cost more.
                  Solo practitioners working from home cost less. Both can be equally effective depending on your needs.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
                  <p class="text-sm"><strong>Price impact:</strong> Same quality lobbyist: Solo practitioner $10K/month vs. Big firm $18K/month for identical work.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

